a deterrent to other violators. He, however, did not give them the option of a fine. He ordered that correctional officers should supervise offenders during the punishment period. Vanguard News Nigeria By Ozioruva Aliu - Benin City The death toll from Coronavirus (COVID-19) in Edo State has climbed to 50, with a total of 1,435 people testing positive for the disease, while 840 persons have been discharged from the state isolation facilities. Commissioner for Health, Dr. Patrick Okundia, also noted that… July 7, 2020 In "News" Edo State Governor, Mr Godwin Obaseki, has said that the state government would deploy the over 800 Police constabulary personnel across the state to enforce strict compliance with the state’s regulations to check the spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19). January 19, 2021 In "Health" THE war against kidnapping in Edo State recorded success, as the state police command, Wednesday, paraded 44 suspected kidnappers including those involved in the recent kidnap of three primary school teachers. August 21, 2013 In "News"